What is attention?
• “Everyone knows what attention is.  It is the 
taking possession by the mind in clear and 
vivid form of one out of what seem several 
simultaneous objects or trains of thought… It 
implies withdrawal from some things in 
order to deal with others.”

‐ William James, 1890

ATTENTION

• awareness/consciousness
• we often attend to more than we realize
• we often attend to less than we realize

ATTENTION & CONSCIOUSNESS
ATTENTION & CONSCIOUSNESS

1. Attention as gatekeeper to perception and knowledge
2. Attention is very limited - one thing at a time
(we miss a lot)
3. Unconscious/Unattended processes 
(do things we not notice influence us?)
4. Some external stimuli “capture” our attention -
“bottom-up” processing
5. Some internal thoughts & goals direct our attention -
“top-down” processing

